parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag can cause serious injury or death, including brain damage, broken bones, and internal injuries.
symptoms: The airbag may deploy with excessive force
causing sharp fragments to be propelled towards the driver and passengers
or the airbag may not deploy at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Repair for Takata Airbag Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of repair parts for the Takata airbag recall can leave drivers and passengers at risk of serious injury or death.
symptoms: Drivers may receive recall notices but be unable to have the repair done due to a lack of available parts
or they may be told to wait for an extended period of time for the repair to be done.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to become difficult to depress, leading to increased stopping distances, and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal is hard to press
the brake pedal makes a hissing or whistling sound
the brake pedal has intermittent pressure
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake pedal goes to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the front seat can cause the seat to move unexpectedly, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The seat bounces forward and backward when stopping or accelerating
the seat makes a loud metal-on-metal slipping noise when turning or braking
the seat shifts backward when accelerating and moves forward when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The high-pitched whistling sound can be a nuisance and potentially damaging to hearing.
symptoms: A high-pitched whistling sound is heard inside and outside the car during the first 15 minutes of driving
the sound is more noticeable in the morning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate seat adjustability can cause discomfort and potentially affect the driver's ability to operate the vehicle safely.
symptoms: The driver's seat does not have sufficient rearward motion
making it difficult for tall drivers with limited range of motion to sit comfortably.
